description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you a dynamic, motivated Assistant Practitioner with demonstrable experience in Sexual Health and Contraception or a Band 3 HCA looking to develop your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If so then, SHiP (Sexual Health in Plymouth) are looking for you to join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SHiP is an integrated Sexual Health and Contraception Service which delivers HIV medicine, sexual health, contraception and termination of pregnancy services citywide across Plymouth and neighbouring areas. We have an exciting opportunity for an experienced Assistant Practitioner to develop their knowledge and skills in these areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Health Care Assistants who have not completed their Assistant Practitioner course are also invited to apply for this post as a training post which will be paid as a Band 3 until completion of the 2 year University Assistant Practitioner course. HCAs wishing to apply must have completed their level 3 or 4 Academic Diploma qualification and have demonstrable experience within sexual health. Qualified Assistant Practitioners are invited to apply for this post as Band 4.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in this exciting opportunity please contact either Senior Sister Claire Forder  ( tel number 01752-437095 or email claireforder@nhs.net) or Nurse Consultant Emma Collins ( tel 01752-439761 or email emma.collins73@nhs.net) .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview date: 23rd November&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;***Preference will be given to internal Trust staff, as well as ‘Priority’ and &#39;At Risk&#39; status including NHS At Risk staff throughout Devon who are able to display recent relevant experience as dictated by the Person Specification.***&lt;/p&gt;
